dispatchPayload(address,uint64,bytes,byt.details: allows state registry to send message via implementation.

params.dstChainId_: is the identifier of the destination chain
params.extraData_: is message amb specific override information
params.message_: is the cross-chain message to be sent
params.srcSender_: is the caller (used for gas refunds)

estimateFees(uint64,bytes,bytes).details: returns the gas fees estimation in native tokens

params.dstChainId_: is the identifier of the destination chain

returns.fees: is the native_tokens to be sent along the transaction

generateExtraData(uint256).details: returns the extra data for the given gas request

params.gasLimit: is the amount of gas limit in wei to override

returns.extraData: is the bytes encoded extra data NOTE: this process is unique to the message bridge

retryPayload(bytes).details: allows for the permissionless calling of the retry mechanism for encoded data

params.data_: is the encoded retry data (different per AMB implementation)

setAxelarConfig(address).details: allows protocol admin to configure axelar gatewaythis allows only one-time configuration for immutability

params.gateway_: is the address of axelar gateway

setAxelarGasService(address,address).details: allows protocol admin to configure axelar gas service and gas estimator

params.gasEstimator_: is the address of axelar gas estimator
params.gasService_: is the address of axelar gas service

setChainId(uint64,string).details: allows protocol admin to add new chain ids in future

params.ambChainId_: is the identifier of the chain given by the AMB NOTE: cannot be defined in an interface as types vary for each message bridge (amb)
params.superChainId_: is the identifier of the chain within superform protocol

setReceiver(string,address).details: allows protocol admin to set receiver implementation on a new chain id

params.ambChainId_: is the identifier of the destination chain within axelar
params.authorizedImpl_: is the implementation of the axelar message bridge on the specified destination NOTE: cannot be defined in an interface as types vary for each message bridge (amb)

estimateFees(uint64,bytes,bytes).notice: not all AMBs will have on-chain estimation for which this function will return 0
